\f7\i \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Quercus
\f4\i0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
), in open ground with grassy cover, and in rocky substrates (see Jordano & Schupp 2000). The adult reproductive trees in the population were mapped and their locations recorded in a GIS database including also the locations of the sampling sites with seed traps (Fig. 5).\
